                <h1>Discovering the Legacy of Samuel</h1>
                <p>Samuel is a captivating name with rich historical significance. In the biblical context, Samuel was a prophet, priest, and one of Israel's last judges, known for anointing the first kings of Israel. The name means "asked of God" or "God has heard," reflecting a deep spiritual connection, making it a popular choice through the ages.</p>
